30 using System;
31 using System.Runtime.InteropServices;
32 using System.Text;
33 using Alis.Core.Aspect.Base.Dll;
34 using Alis.Core.Input.Properties;
35 
36 namespace Alis.Core.Input.SDL2
37 {
41  public static class Sdl
42  {
46  static Sdl()
47  {
48  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.OSX))
49  {
50  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
51  {
52  case Architecture.Arm64:
53  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.dylib", NativeInput.osx_arm64_SDL2);
54  break;
55  case Architecture.X64:
56  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.dylib", NativeInput.osx_x64_SDL2);
57  break;
58  }
59  }
60 
61  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
62  {
63  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
64  {
65  case Architecture.Arm64:
66  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.dll", NativeInput.win_x64_SDL2);
67  break;
68  case Architecture.X64:
69  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.dll", NativeInput.win_x64_SDL2);
70  break;
71  case Architecture.X86:
72  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.dll", NativeInput.win_x86_SDL2);
73  break;
74  }
75  }
76 
77  if (RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Linux))
78  {
79  switch (RuntimeInformation.ProcessArchitecture)
80  {
81  case Architecture.Arm64:
82  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.so", NativeInput.linux_arm64_SDL2);
83  break;
84  case Architecture.X64:
85  EmbeddedDllClass.ExtractEmbeddedDlls("SDL2.so", NativeInput.linux_x64_SDL2);
86  break;
87  }
88  }
89  }

94  * Only available in 2.0.4 or higher.
95  */

1980 
1981  /* Used for stack allocated string marshaling. */
1987  internal static int Utf8Size(string str)
1988  {
1989  if (str == null)
1990  {
1991  return 0;
1992  }
1993 
1994  return str.Length * 4 + 1;
1995  }
1996 
2004  internal static unsafe byte* Utf8Encode(string str, byte* buffer, int bufferSize)
2005  {
2006  if (str == null)
2007  {
2008  return (byte*) 0;
2009  }
2010 
2011  fixed (char* strPtr = str)
2012  {
2013  Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(strPtr, str.Length + 1, buffer, bufferSize);
2014  }
2015 
2016  return buffer;
2017  }
2018 
2019  /* Used for heap allocated string marshaling.
2020  * Returned byte* must be free'd with FreeHGlobal.
2021  */
2027  internal static unsafe byte* Utf8EncodeHeap(string str)
2028  {
2029  if (str == null)
2030  {
2031  return (byte*) 0;
2032  }
2033 
2034  int bufferSize = Utf8Size(str);
2035  byte* buffer = (byte*) Marshal.AllocHGlobal(bufferSize);
2036  fixed (char* strPtr = str)
2037  {
2038  Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(strPtr, str.Length + 1, buffer, bufferSize);
2039  }
2040 
2041  return buffer;
2042  }
2043 
2044  /* This is public because SDL_DropEvent needs it! */
2051  public static unsafe string UTF8_ToManaged(IntPtr s, bool freePtr = false)
2052  {
2053  if (s == IntPtr.Zero)
2054  {
2055  return null;
2056  }
2057 
2058  /* We get to do strlen ourselves! */
2059  byte* ptr = (byte*) s;
2060  while (*ptr != 0)
2061  {
2062  ptr++;
2063  }
2064 
2065  /* TODO: This #ifdef is only here because the equivalent
2066  * .NET 2.0 constructor appears to be less efficient?
2067  * Here's the pretty version, maybe steal this instead:
2068  *
2069  string result = new string(
2070  (sbyte*) s, // Also, why sbyte???
2071  0,
2072  (int) (ptr - (byte*) s),
2073  System.Text.Encoding.UTF8
2074  );
2075  * See the CoreCLR source for more info.
2076  * -flibit
2077  */
2078 #if NETSTANDARD2_0
2079  /* Modern C# lets you just send the byte*, nice! */
2080  string result = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString(
2081  (byte*) s,
2082  (int) (ptr - (byte*) s)
2083  );
2084 #else
2085  /* Old C# requires an extra memcpy, bleh! */
2086  int len = (int) (ptr - (byte*) s);
2087  if (len == 0)
2088  {
2089  return string.Empty;
2090  }
2091 
2092  char* chars = stackalloc char[len];
2093  int strLen = Encoding.UTF8.GetChars((byte*) s, len, chars, len);
2094  string result = new string(chars, 0, strLen);
2095 #endif
2096 
2097  /* Some SDL functions will malloc, we have to free! */
2098  if (freePtr)
2099  {
2100  SDL_free(s);
2101  }
2102 
2103  return result;
2104  }

2115  public static uint SDL_FOURCC(byte a, byte b, byte c, byte d) => (uint) (a | (b << 8) | (c << 16) | (d << 24));

2134  /* Buffer.BlockCopy is not available in every runtime yet. Also,
2135  * using memcpy directly can be a compatibility issue in other
2136  * strange ways. So, we expose this to get around all that.
2137  * -flibit
2138  */
2146  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
2147  public static extern IntPtr SDL_memcpy(IntPtr dst, IntPtr src, IntPtr len);

2149  /* IntPtr refers to an SDL_RWops* */
2156  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_RWFromFile", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
2157  private static extern unsafe IntPtr INTERNAL_SDL_RWFromFile(
2158  byte* file,
2159  byte* mode
2160  );
2161 
2168  public static unsafe IntPtr SDL_RWFromFile(
2169  string file,
2170  string mode
2171  )
2172  {
2173  byte* utf8File = Utf8EncodeHeap(file);
2174  byte* utf8Mode = Utf8EncodeHeap(mode);
2175  IntPtr rwOps = INTERNAL_SDL_RWFromFile(
2176  utf8File,
2177  utf8Mode
2178  );
2179  Marshal.FreeHGlobal((IntPtr) utf8Mode);
2180  Marshal.FreeHGlobal((IntPtr) utf8File);
2181  return rwOps;
2182  }

3108  [DllImport(NativeLibName, EntryPoint = "SDL_ShowMessageBox", CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
3109  private static extern int INTERNAL_SDL_ShowMessageBox([In] ref InternalSdlMessageBoxData messageboxdata, out int buttonid);
3110 
3111  /* Ripped from Jameson's LpUtf8StrMarshaler */
3117  private static IntPtr INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(string str)
3118  {
3119  if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(str))
3120  {
3121  return IntPtr.Zero;
3122  }
3123 
3124  byte[] bytes = Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(str + '\0');
3125  IntPtr mem = SDL_malloc((IntPtr) bytes.Length);
3126  Marshal.Copy(bytes, 0, mem, bytes.Length);
3127  return mem;
3128  }
3129 
3136  public static unsafe int SDL_ShowMessageBox([In] ref SdlMessageBoxData messageboxdata, out int buttonid)
3137  {
3138  InternalSdlMessageBoxData data = new InternalSdlMessageBoxData
3139  {
3140  flags = messageboxdata.flags,
3141  window = messageboxdata.window,
3142  title = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.title),
3143  message = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.message),
3144  numbuttons = messageboxdata.numbuttons
3145  };
3146 
3147  InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData[] buttons = new InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData[messageboxdata.numbuttons];
3148  for (int i = 0; i < messageboxdata.numbuttons; i++)
3149  {
3150  buttons[i] = new InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData
3151  {
3152  flags = messageboxdata.buttons[i].flags,
3153  buttonid = messageboxdata.buttons[i].buttonid,
3154  text = INTERNAL_AllocUTF8(messageboxdata.buttons[i].text)
3155  };
3156  }
3157 
3158  if (messageboxdata.colorScheme != null)
3159  {
3160  data.colorScheme = Marshal.AllocHGlobal(Marshal.SizeOf(typeof(SdlMessageBoxColorScheme)));
3161  Marshal.StructureToPtr(messageboxdata.colorScheme.Value, data.colorScheme, false);
3162  }
3163 
3164  int result;
3165  fixed (InternalSdlMessageBoxButtonData* buttonsPtr = &buttons[0])
3166  {
3167  data.buttons = (IntPtr) buttonsPtr;
3168  result = INTERNAL_SDL_ShowMessageBox(ref data, out buttonid);
3169  }
3170 
3171  Marshal.FreeHGlobal(data.colorScheme);
3172  for (int i = 0; i < messageboxdata.numbuttons; i++)
3173  {
3174  SDL_free(buttons[i].text);
3175  }
3176 
3177  SDL_free(data.message);
3178  SDL_free(data.title);
3179 
3180  return result;
3181  }

6615  public static uint SDL_DEFINE_PIXELFOURCC(byte a, byte b, byte c, byte d) => SDL_FOURCC(a, b, c, d);
6616 
6626  public static uint SDL_DEFINE_PIXELFORMAT(
6627  SdlPixelType type,
6628  uint order,
6629  SdlPackedLayout layout,
6630  byte bits,
6631  byte bytes
6632  )
6633  => (uint) (
6634  (1 << 28) |
6635  ((byte) type << 24) |
6636  ((byte) order << 20) |
6637  ((byte) layout << 16) |
6638  (bits << 8) |
6639  bytes
6640  );
6641 
6647  public static byte SDL_PIXELFLAG(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 28) & 0x0F);
6648 
6654  public static byte SDL_PIXELTYPE(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 24) & 0x0F);
6655 
6661  public static byte SDL_PIXELORDER(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 20) & 0x0F);
6662 
6668  public static byte SDL_PIXELLAYOUT(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 16) & 0x0F);
6669 
6675  public static byte SDL_BITSPERPIXEL(uint x) => (byte) ((x >> 8) & 0xFF);
6676 
6682  public static byte SDL_BYTESPERPIXEL(uint x)
6683  {
6684  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(x))
6685  {
6686  if (x == SdlPixelformatYuy2 ||
6687  x == SdlPixelformatUyvy ||
6688  x == SdlPixelformatYvyu)
6689  {
6690  return 2;
6691  }
6692 
6693  return 1;
6694  }
6695 
6696  return (byte) (x & 0xFF);
6697  }

6704  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_INDEXED(uint format)
6705  {
6706  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
6707  {
6708  return false;
6709  }
6710 
6711  SdlPixelType pType =
6712  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
6713  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex1 ||
6714  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex4 ||
6715  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeIndex8;
6716  }
6717 
6723  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_PACKED(uint format)
6724  {
6725  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
6726  {
6727  return false;
6728  }
6729 
6730  SdlPixelType pType =
6731  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
6732  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked8 ||
6733  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked16 ||
6734  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypePacked32;
6735  }
6736 
6742  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ARRAY(uint format)
6743  {
6744  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_FOURCC(format))
6745  {
6746  return false;
6747  }
6748 
6749  SdlPixelType pType =
6750  (SdlPixelType) SDL_PIXELTYPE(format);
6751  return pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu8 ||
6752  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu16 ||
6753  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayu32 ||
6754  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayf16 ||
6755  pType == SdlPixelType.SdlPixeltypeArrayf32;
6756  }

6763  public static bool SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ALPHA(uint format)
6764  {
6765  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_PACKED(format))
6766  {
6767  SdlPackedOrder pOrder =
6768  (SdlPackedOrder) SDL_PIXELORDER(format);
6769  return pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderArgb ||
6770  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderRgba ||
6771  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderAbgr ||
6772  pOrder == SdlPackedOrder.SdlPackedorderBgra;
6773  }
6774 
6775  if (SDL_ISPIXELFORMAT_ARRAY(format))
6776  {
6777  SdlArrayOrder aOrder =
6778  (SdlArrayOrder) SDL_PIXELORDER(format);
6779  return aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderArgb ||
6780  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderRgba ||
6781  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderAbgr ||
6782  aOrder == SdlArrayOrder.SdlArrayorderBgra;
6783  }
6784 
6785  return false;
6786  }

8058  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]

8060  SdlEventFilter filter,
8061  IntPtr userdata
8062  );
8063 
8064  /* userdata refers to a void* */
8071  [DllImport(NativeLibName, CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl)]
8072  private static extern SdlBool SDL_GetEventFilter(
8073  out IntPtr filter,
8074  out IntPtr userdata
8075  );
8076 
8083  public static SdlBool SDL_GetEventFilter(
8084  out SdlEventFilter filter,
8085  out IntPtr userdata
8086  )
8087  {
8088  IntPtr result = IntPtr.Zero;
8089  SdlBool retval = SDL_GetEventFilter(out result, out userdata);
8090  if (result != IntPtr.Zero)
8091  {
8092  filter = (SdlEventFilter) Marshal.GetDelegateForFunctionPointer(
8093  result,
8094  typeof(SdlEventFilter)
8095  );
8096  }
8097  else
8098  {
8099  filter = null;
8100  }
8101 
8102  return retval;
8103  }

9697  IntPtr gamecontroller,
9698  SdlGameControllerAxis axis
9699  )
9700  {

9705  );
